Acetate Goggles Frame : 1900/-
Check-up: Rs.200/-

The place is pretty good. The doctors explain the issues well. Goggles Service is fast as well. But for me personally, the visit to Metro did not work out as I had a very weird blurry vision in the right eye after the glass change. The Synchrony HMC blue glass somehow gave me blurry vision in my right eye when my eye pupil is not focusing at the center of the glass. There are only a few angles where I can see clearly.

I have never had such issue before. But with this new glass, if i focus even a litle bit out of the center, if i try to look even a litle sideways without turning my head, the right eye is completely blurry. It has been very annoying.

I went for the recheckup, explained the issue and was told that it could be due to the Goggles Frame being a little bend. So, I changed the frame as well,but I am still having the same issue.

I do not know if it is due to faulty glass, or somehow the glass was offcentered during fitting but it just doesn't feel right. The optical guys were also very professional and helpful, and I am sure that they do their job very well. But Metro did not work out for me. I will be changing my glasses someplace else.

But, yes You guys can go here for check up, it is very well maintained.","Images":null,"When":""}]

Chaotically wonderful, with narrow streets packed full of stalls selling a huge variety of goods, it‚Äôs a fascinating place to wander and soak up everyday city life.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhCEnEr0ErT2ww4bdVtB17Ny&fid=0x0:0x76fc820ef1d6df3a"],"When":"2025-12-29"},{"Name":"MT","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJFf5BdfA-kUzHUWgOxqjgYA9-T2F2f_cdQnDzdfG7vx6loxDw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Busy local market. Very busy where pedestrians, motorcycles and cars share the same narrow street.
It was fun though experiencing local life. You will walk shoulder to shoulder with locals. Dusty hence make sure you have a face mask.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhDqahtoyqNdt5yh9czwq_br&fid=0x0:0x76fc820ef1d6df3a"],"When":"2025-12-22"},{"Name":"Dikendra Giri","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU8Km0t4afZHwTUw8M9YDkYRUEWZ-dvyO65lCRWh_aI_7s6Kncs=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A visit to Ason Bazaar is like stepping into the soul of Kathmandu. This historic marketplace, located in the heart of the old city, is one of the most vibrant, colorful, and culturally rich places in Nepal. Ason is not just a market; it is a living museum where daily life, tradition, trade, and history come together in the most authentic way.

As soon as you enter Ason, your senses are awakened. The narrow streets are filled with shops selling everything imaginable ‚Äî spices, grains, lentils, vegetables, fruits, flowers, utensils, traditional lamps, religious items, and local snacks. The aroma of spices, incense, and fresh produce fills the air, while vendors loudly call out their prices, creating an energetic and lively atmosphere. It can feel chaotic at first, but that chaos is what makes Ason special and unforgettable.

One of the most beautiful aspects of Ason Bazaar is how deeply it reflects Newari culture. Surrounded by ancient temples, shrines, and traditional buildings, the market feels sacred and historical at the same time. The nearby Annapurna Temple and various small shrines remind visitors that spirituality is woven into everyday life here.

Ason is also an excellent place to experience local life and photography, though visitors should be respectful, as it is a working market. Prices are reasonable, and bargaining is common, adding to the fun of shopping.

If you truly want to understand Kathmandu beyond tourist attractions, Ason Bazaar is a must-visit. It‚Äôs loud, crowded, colorful, and absolutely full of life ‚Äî a place that stays in your memory long after you leave.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kat Saleh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVw9aDtmORaWlYzQ9GxdhrmX_CJIGoKGPNn93rXEiHeQI6vRlf6_Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very lovely place to shopping for the other 'world' style. title: Pashupati Homeopathic Hospital
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Jenish World","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXya1Vf9_gKQ8t6bg_jV5-9oGKHFOrjqNxbA0Ty2vnb2vOFDlk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Pashupati Homoeopathic Hospital HariharBhawan, Lalitpur.
Pashupati Homoeopathic Hospital is a government hospital where treatment is free of charge.  All skin related treatments can be done here for free.  If you are going to this hospital for the first time, you will have to register your name in room number 6 and after registering your name, you will be given a paper and after taking the paper, go to the mentioned room and consult with the doctor and submit the medicine details written by the doctor to the medicine registration class of room number 6 and from the medicine room  The health worker will say the name written on the paper and the medicine will be given to you.  Most of the medicines here are in tablets, pills and liquids.  Although they look the same, the strength of the medicine varies according to the disease.  Thousands of patients come here daily. (You can visit here from sharp 10 am till 3 Pm. and also the  break will be at 1:30 to 2 PM)
All the health workers including the assistant doctor, the people working in this homeopathic hospital are very nice,& kind helpful, I liked it a lot.
Diseases treated in this hospital mentioned below :üëá
1. Cough, asthma, chest related
2. Relating to the skin (chai, poto, musa, dubi, dandifor).
3. Relating to the digestive system (stomach).
4. Related to stones (kidney, gall bladder).
5. Diabetes related
6. Arthritis, uric acid, rheumatism
7. Related to high blood pressure (blood pressure).
9. Related to headaches, migraines and migraines
10. Relating to alkai (piles), fistulas and fissures
11. Nose, Ear, Throat
12. Reproductive health and sexually transmitted diseases
13. Women's and Children's Diseases
14. Related to mental illness (stress, insomnia).
15. Relating to body folds, nodules, cysts, lipomas
16. Urinary and prostate related
17. Treatment of other diseases and proper advice

Recommend to visit here if you have related health diseases  problems.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIHM0ogKEICAgIDPzr_Oaw&fid=0x0:0x845be7ad9c4fcb43"],"When":"2024-12-2"},{"Name":"Aarif ‚Äúlinuxaarif‚Äù Khan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI3BNxeoLMfQdcqlv9OIQ3aht6xVeKBZAO91Bzkmv_pBEJXKyo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Only one struggling "Homoeopathic Hospital" in Nepal. It is a Government based free hospital with less budget and no funding but still striving to provides best service with minimal resources.

Approx 600 - 1000 patients visit each day for health check up and other disease. It is very well known for curing General Skin disease and Warts and good thing is that there are no side effects but it takes some time to take effect.

However, this hospital has 3 Doctors and handful nurse, yet they have been providing one of the best service comparing to other big hospital such as: Bir Hospital, Patan Hospital.

The senior Doctor of this hospital is "Dr. Shabbir Khan" who has been working and providing service for past 2 decades. Its impressive to see these doctors work so fluently with so less resources and yet keep their patients happy.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Manoj Bajracharya","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWFMN9T_r9ubHl76kuVmk2GrEhVRM3s2xUBFyhZ9wDr9dhQSwc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"There is no doubt that it is one and only homeopathy hospital, Sorry clinic in lalitpur totally operated under government aid, but those public relation officers and staffs had no manners to talk with costumers, they fill as the president of homeopathy sector, first of all request to the department head to give the public relation training to those all government staffs including medicine distribution head and department staffs. We consulted Dr. Mamata Baral, Senior Consultant Gynaecologist, who was kind, caring, and highly professional. She took time to listen carefully, explained every detail with patience, and made us feel very comfortable throughout the consultation. Her friendly approach and expertise gave us great confidence and peace of mind.

We stayed in a deluxe room, which was spacious, neat, and well-maintained, with all the essential facilities for a pleasant stay. The nursing staff and support team were also very courteous, attentive, and always ready to help with a smile.

Ltd. in Chabhil for my mother's check-up, and I was very impressed with the overall experience. The hospital is well-equipped and maintained, providing a clean and comfortable environment for patients and visitors alike.

The doctors and nurses were highly professional and attentive. They took the time to explain the diagnosis and treatment options clearly, which helped us feel more at ease. She visits different doctors from here.

Despite the hospital being busy, the check-in and consultation process was smooth and efficient. We didn't have to wait long, and the staff managed everything promptly.

Cash counters could be more efficient. Registration and billing for services require to stay in line which causes delay in service delivery. A separate line could help ease the congestion during peak times.

The hospital has a wide range of medical services and specialties, ensuring that different healthcare needs can be met under one roof. The hospital was very clean and well-maintained, which is crucial for a healthcare facility.

Adequate waiting space for different departments is also there which makes it look less crowded.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIHM0ogKEICAgIDXqvDsWA&fid=0x0:0x61a8a608eeb02b85"],"When":"2024-10-26"},{"Name":"S K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWgpy738obi0HSO6StBfjVmIc-LXQr70_VCFIPOv5s_22xGwz7Fxw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Om Hospital provides a mixed experience for patients seeking general check-ups and medical care. The facility boasts decent doctors and rooms, but falls short in several areas.

Starting with the positives, the hospital's exterior, reception, and immediate assistance for wheelchair-bound patients are commendable. The staff's dedication to helping patients navigate the facility is a notable highlight.

However, shortcomings become apparent upon closer examination. While the hospital's appearance is pleasing, the cleanliness and hygiene standards within the cabins leave much to be desired. Additionally, some doctors exhibit rushed consultations and lack friendliness, with one notable instance of a doctor neglecting basic patient courtesy.

While the X-ray department stands out for its competent staff, the pharmacy disappoints with its tendency to overcharge for medications. Despite addressing concerns, the pharmacy fails to rectify pricing errors, eroding trust in its services.

On a brighter note, the hospital's small caf√© offers a pleasant respite, with the banana cake receiving particular praise.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIHM0ogKEICAgICT6LDm_gE&fid=0x0:0x61a8a608eeb02b85"],"When":"2024-5-10"},{"Name":"Madan Kumar Adhikari","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV_UZnhEX8_ksMLE8IRV37SmB9JQxONjdBDoAwrq20igBAxCF7uuQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"My experience Om Hospital, Chabahil, Kathmandu was exceptional. title: Transport Management Office, Driving License, Ekantakuna
address: M886+4G6 Transport Management Office, Driving License, Ekantakuna, Ring Rd, Lalitpur 44600
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Upendra Bagale","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWT12DFtq6DBzUgzwA1UfroDaQ-9BOpg05-mr0mH2O9S5wR36Pc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I visited the transport office several times in May and June 2025 for my car license. Overall, my experience was neither good nor bad, but I felt that things could be much simpler if there were better management and development. Unfortunately, I witnessed clear signs of corruption. Some staff members seemed to be in contact with third parties arranging ‚Äúsettings.‚Äù A few people even approached me in the parking area, offering to get me a license without taking any exams for 40,000, which was shocking to see happening right outside a government office.

The staff inside the office appeared to lack basic civic sense and professionalism. There was poor communication and inefficient service, making even simple tasks unnecessarily difficult, as if we were asking for personal favors. Despite these issues, my driving test itself was a good experience. However, seeing open corruption around the process was disappointing. I really hope the system improves in the future.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhDtQLdqcOn6UNTUE5CIKtBm&fid=0x0:0xa51dc05f41faa05d"],"When":"2025-11-11"},{"Name":"Jenish World","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXya1Vf9_gKQ8t6bg_jV5-9oGKHFOrjqNxbA0Ty2vnb2vOFDlk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"When I think of a government office, many negative things come to mind, such as slow and disorganized service delivery. However, the last time I went here to get my new driver's license, I felt that it was very fast and efficient. All the services for citizen grievance redressal, including citizen inquiry rooms, have been expanded here. I got a good experience and service here.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhDSFDqfJNUFhBU73PMCTyPm&fid=0x0:0xa51dc05f41faa05d"],"When":"2025-7-18"},{"Name":"Ramesh Bhurtel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVj3F6jNVYzDvql5TaeX_uV5VeIxxvVnsabNkDGWfM6TASoz4xa=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"We all come here to pay taxes to the government. After getting the service almost everyone feels like they won a battle.
For what?
The online application is meant for applicants given priority. Why don't they provide an exact, pre-fixed time to avoid the crowd?
Such a chaotic place,
One of the poorly managed government offices.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhBtmGkEVINwxawsGVSDBoxk&fid=0x0:0xa51dc05f41faa05d"],"When":"2025-6-29"},{"Name":"Bishnu Dhakal","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXB8FyTAUyihRyKKzcT04KYiwHw8kky86GD4jt5sAHy0vOxW517=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I had another mixed experience with a government service. I visited the Vehicle Tax, Yatayat Office in Ekantakuna, Lalitpur. Despite the busy schedule, the service, (Paying tax, renewing, green stamp, etc.) was surprisingly quick and efficient. However, some staff acted more like they were in charge rather than offering helpful guidance. Still, I appreciate the service provided for in a respective sequence.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIHM0ogKEICAgICn49bmxAE&fid=0x0:0xa51dc05f41faa05d"],"When":"2024-9-29"},{"Name":"SamBeg StHa1","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVPhXuXBLmniTm5Ajit-4nPCHUDT5FRU8SQOoQBhmtITAD1B9k2Zw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Poor management, and ignorant service officers.

Edit 2024: Service has gotten better since the last visit, the so-called brokers now don't seem to appear. However, still the ignorant (mostly indifferent) service workers still make the process annoying. I went there to renew my licence, most of the process watch hitch free but the bank employee where we deposited the money irked me to the extreme. I went to pay with the money and she said "you need to fill a voucher". That's it. Inexperienced me, cumbered with not missing out on my line didn't know anything and went to a completely different bank outlet (yes there were two) and filled up everything on the voucher and turns out I didn't need to go anywhere, the voucher was right in front in the previous place. The worker didn't feel the need to explain anything to me and I even asked what I needed to do. I guess it was miscommunication on my part but at least try to be a bit helpful and explain. I guess they're human and they do this with hundreds every day which makes it inconvenient for them but her nonchalance wasted my 30 mins. So, I still rate the service badly since almost everyone who'll visit is like me who doesn't know much.

I guess the need to embrace technology in cases like these is very exigent and I hope a day comes where I don't have to deal with humans for government services. Sad for humanity but these workers make it painful.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIHM0ogKEICAgICv6KTLBw&fid=0x0:0xa51dc05f41faa05d"],"When":"2024-12-7"},{"Name":"Prayash Phuyal","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVvwbshUPHoKa5Z33T4F-_xBkH3In6qsArlIPP1vGQDyo1qKF4s=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"A typical government office experience.
It's a tough day out getting your job done here walking around, jumping between rooms, struggling to find the right places and waiting for hours when crowded.
All that to hear rude and unhelpful voices from some employees who only ever talk to you after you ask questions.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIHM0ogKEICAgICZ3O_dOA&fid=0x0:0xa51dc05f41faa05d"],"When":"2023-9-6"},{"Name":"Surya Chaudhary","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXzkCW46CDX4LtTI3K98v3u8h7PuIN18RQnSWrZu2q_ddVojn-x=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Now office is operating and renew license is going on
Let's hope we will get new update very soon","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sCIABIhD_ShMbuJfKRJPb_0pQUFfu&fid=0x0:0xa51dc05f41faa05d"],"When":"2025-11-6"},{"Name":"Wolf pack","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUEK54g-Px5wAXUm5oV3SltgHtQB_wg8w-t55DcK0iOQC1M5gI=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Really Impressed at how efficient the system has been. It is easy to renew license without having to use a middle man. The whole process was done in Under 10 minutes. I had taken my Original Citizenship and old license that‚Äôs it. No need to fill forms, no hassle. Absolutely, Impressed by whole process. During my last renewal, things weren‚Äôt this simple and easy.","Images":null,"When":""}]
